author: Russell Brand
description:
LA erupts in chaos after ICE raids spark days of unrest—and the National Guard is called in. But is this spontaneous civil action or a staged distraction? Russell breaks down Gavin Newsom’s hypocrisy, from lockdown tyranny to open-air drug dens, and questions whether California’s collapse is accidental—or by design. With insight from Michael Shellenberger, we explore how compassion has been weaponized, laws abandoned, and order inverted. Are we witnessing a true civil breakdown… or something more orchestrated?
